Vice President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo has expressed utter displeasure over the harassment of Nigerians by operatives of the Federal Special Anti-Robbery Squad (FSARS).  The Vice President, who spoke to State House Correspondents during the weekend in Abuja, also condemned the routine harassment and maimings of young Nigerians by operatives of the FSARS, describing the development as infuriating and unacceptable.  Our State House Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Vice President also commended the Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Mohammed Adamu, for banning routine patrol of the FSARS and other tactical squads of the Nigeria Police Force (NPF). He equally implored Nigerians to always bring the attention of the government to police officers unprofessional behaviours.